arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
1.70 m north south -by- 2.80 m east west.

This collapse locus is unique in that it appears to be somewhat intact. Presumably, during the main collapse period of the complex a whole section of the building (likely part of Locus 57) dislodged and fell into the entrance room. Still held together by mortar, the ashlars were rough-cut and inexpertly laid.
Intact collapse in the northwest of the entrance room
